text: Paratrachelas is a genus of araneomorph spiders in the family Trachelidae, first described by M. M. Kovblyuk & A. A. Nadolny in 2009. ==Species== it contains five species: *Paratrachelas acuminus (Zhu & An, 1988) — Russia (Far East), China, Korea *Paratrachelas atlantis Bosselaers & Bosmans, 2010 — Algeria *Paratrachelas ibericus (Bosselaers, Urones, Barrientos & Alberdi, 2009) — Portugal, Spain, France, Algeria *Paratrachelas maculatus (Thorell, 1875) — France to Ukraine, Turkey, Israel *Paratrachelas validus (Simon, 1884) — Portugal, Spain, Italy ==References== ==External links== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Trachelidae
title: Paratrachelas
